93. In this Part— 

“market operator” means a market operator of a regulated market authorised 
under Regulation 56(1)(a) of the MiFID Regulations; 

“Common Equity Tier 1 capital” has the meaning set out in Regulation 31(3), 
substituting ‘fund administrator’ for ‘market operator’ where necessary; 

“basic capital requirement” means the amount arising from the calculation 
under Regulation 95; 

“systemic capital add-on” means the amount referred to under Regulation 97; 

“Market Operator Risk and Capital Adequacy 
(MORCAAP) amount” means the amount specified under Regulation 96. 

